SIMPLE: foul-mouthed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foul-mouthed
<hw>Foul"-mouthed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Using language
scurrilous, opprobrious, obscene, or profane; abusive; <as>as, noisy
<ex>foul-mouthed</ex> women all shouting at once</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> foul-spoken.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>foul-mouthed</qex> a witness never appeared in any
cause.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foulness</ent>⟦br⟧
